</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4154 Almighty God Your Word Is Cast (C major)
Key: C (no accidentals). Straightforward tonal hymn, bright major key.

m.1: I/vi — "33" open pairs, LH C2-G2-C3-E3 establishes ground
m.2: ii7→V — full ii7 "333" LH 4-note, then V "33"
m.3: vi→V — Am then G diatonic sub for D (F# stays in melody only)
m.4: V → V7 — arpeggiated arpeggio in LH passing G-D-G / G-B-F for V7 color
m.5: I→ii — climbing RH to D5 for phrase peak
m.6: I→iii — Em substitution, contrary motion hands
m.7: ii→V pre-final — LH walks bass D→G, building for cadence
m.8: I final — all sustained, wide C-to-C spread with E5 in RH

VOICE LEADING: F4→E4→D4 inner-voice descent in RH across mm.5-7 mirrors
  descending bass. Leading tone B4→C5 in m.7→m.8 RH resolves cleanly.

TEXTURE ARC: Opens moderate, builds phrase by phrase, climax at m.8 C5/E5.
-->
